The global Aerospace Magnesium Alloys market size is estimated to be worth US$ 180.85 million in 2022 and is forecast to a readjusted size of US$ 277.1 million by 2028 with a CAGR of 7.37% during the forecast period 2022-2028.



Aerospace magnesium alloys are used in aircraft, missiles and spacecraft. These alloys are essential for the structural integrity of airframes and engines due to their light weight and high tensile strength.

